He said: 'The night before coming in I had second thoughts but I knew I had to do it. I wanted to be known as an actor and an athlete but I was known for my sex life.

'When I came in I treated it like a fight and turned boos into cheers,' he told the Daily Star.

2007 winner Brian Belo also attended, comparing the site to an exclusive private school.

He said: 'It's surreal really. I feel like I'm an old Etonian visiting the school again.'

Visitors will be able to have a look around the house at Elstree Studios in Borehamwood, Hertfordshire, for just two days. The 500 tickets sold out within 12 minutes.

