The
National Trust’s London director Ivo Dawnay said: 'The fact that the 
housemates’ residence is not, say, a sublime late Robert Adam country 
house does not necessarily make it less interesting.

'The great houses of our past reflected the tastes of the day and so does the Big Brother House.'

